  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 190°C/ 170°C (fan)/ gas 5</p><p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half, then into triangles</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>garlic </strong>in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>hazelnuts</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684496337148-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684496337148-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684496337148-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684496337148-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684496337148-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ciabatta triangles</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 7-10 min or until the ciabatta is starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684496343070-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684496343070-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684496343070-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684496343070-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684496343070-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Grate the<strong> sliced tomatoes</strong>, on the sliced-side,<strong> </strong>into a shallow bowl until you are left with just the skin – this is your <strong>tomato pulp</strong></p><p>Tip: Keep your palm flat while grating!</p><p>Discard the<strong> tomato skin</strong></p><p>Set a fine sieve over a large bowl and drain the <strong>tomato pulp</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684496346220-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684496346220-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684496346220-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684496346220-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684496346220-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained tomato pulp </strong>to the shallow bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>– this is your<strong> tomate topping</strong></p><p>Set aside the bowl with the<strong> tomato juice </strong>for later</p><p>Once the ciabatta is starting to brown, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>chopped hazelnuts </strong>to the side, then return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-4 min or until toasted (watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!) – this is your <strong>toasted ciabatta </strong>and<strong> toasted hazelnuts</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684496350024-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684496350024-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
